name: 001 - Landscapes | Paraná River
description:
This was taken like two years ago. I went to the Paraná River island, crossing from Rosario, Santa Fe to Victoria, Entre Ríos. This is a normal destination for the people here in Ros.

I used my very first 35mm reflex camera, the Canon EF with a 50mm f1.4 lens ✨

About the film, it was an expired cine Fuji Eterna 500T, that's why the color. This film is balanced to be used with tungsten lights (actually u can figure it out because the T in the name), so the outdoor photos takes that cold blue color, good for experimenting, but in that case, I had not idea about that film property.
